{"questionId":"25799","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math>, find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>one of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>B</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>36</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b920077c5f766b5a0510ddc7619be165fd120f88.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to equate their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> with their expression for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>B</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mi>B</mi></mfenced><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>36</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><stro